Eh. I didn't get a whole lot out of this, to be honest.

While the idea of Santa Anna as a time-traveling reality bender is somewhat interesting, as is the Foundation reaching out to a past predecessor in an attempt to pass the buck, the bulk of the narrative itself boils down to so much dry  without a whole lot of characterization of Santa Anna or the Foundation to make me care for the outcome, which is fairly essential for a character-focused piece as this.

No vote. Several nuggets here are good, but they don't fully solidify for me as a reader.







